commit 945d357aac34892ccb53c2daa1815ebd0d7679fe
Author: Greg Marra <greg.marra@gmail.com>
Date:   2018-04-01 17:04:17 -0700

    Fix Instagram Thumbnails (#2220)
    
    * Update team badges to use v3 API and other cleanup
    
    My goal was to stay as close to the original TBA team badges as
    possible. Because there is no single equivalent v3 API call, this now
    needs to make multiple API calls and is twice as slow due to that
    (~1sec).
    
    You will need to create a `config.php` file with the X-TBA-Auth-Key for
    making API requests.
    
    The generated teamoverlays and gradients directories are now commited to
    git to keep the local tree clean when testing.
    
    * Fix instagram thumbnails. Fixes #2219

commit af619842126c232171fd90b43b894ab0f32189a9
Author: Brian Rozmierski <bdaroz@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   2017-06-25 16:16:51 -0400

    API v3 Doc Update (#1947)
    
    * Description and redundancy fixes.
    
    The descriptions have been updated slightly to clarify meaning and
    to correct grammar.
    
    The `district` property in the `Event` models has been replaced with
    a link to the `District_List` model, which was identical.
    
    * Required Fields Pass & District_Ranking Model Docs
    
    All fields in *fully-documented* models now have a `required` field list
    that represents those fields that may not be `null`.
    
    `District_Ranking` model is now documented.
    
    * Revert multi-line JSON field as out-of-spec.
    
    The multi-line `description` field atop the swagger spec included
    the newline character, making it a multi-line string. Control characters
    are not allowed in JSON strings and must be escaped.

255	157	static/swagger/api_v3.json

    Admin Panel Interface for Registration Days (#1650)

    /tasks/admin/enqueue/registration_day/YYYY-mm-dd/year/interval

    "turbo mode" sitevar to reduce caches to be active from now until the

    Improve deployment pipeline (#1574)
    
    This addresses some of the issues raised in #1568. Specifically:
     - takes the target app engine module as a parameter
     - allows setting a --reauth flag so you can choose which account to use
       when deploying
     - by default checks for the travis build to have succeeded beore
       deploying. Bypass with --yolo
    
    For example, I can deploy tba.lopreiato.me with `paver deploy -d
    ~/google_appengine -p tba-dev-phil`
    
    Closes #1568

commit c36830c9d85845510008bf011b75327c4990d285
Author: Phil Lopreiato <phil-lopreiato@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   2016-04-11 18:04:53 -0400

    Support Octofinals in FMSAPI Parsers (#1461)
    
    * Update FMSAPI Match Parser to Include Octofinals
    
    This modifies the parser to check the description for the first match
    returned. If it contains the word 'Octofinal', use special numbering.
    
    We can do this because we hit/parse each endpoint independently, and the
    API typically returns matches in play order, so the octofinals will
    always be first. So I think this is a safe assumption
    
    Closes #1436
    
    * Add tests for FMSAPI Match parser
    
    * Add tests to cover FMSAPI Alliances Parser
    
    Includes case where we get 16 alliances back
    
    * Support octofinals in MatchDetailParser
    
    We can't actually yet determine if we're dealing with octofinals, since
    we only have match number to go by. Not sure what to do here...
    
    * Test MatchDetailsParser

Author: Phil Lopreiato <plnyyanks@gmail.com>

    Update datafeed tests to include website parsing
    
    One interesting issue: when urlparse handles a url without a scheme,
    it'll reutrn a url formatted with http:///. This shouldn't be an issue,
    since browsers will ignore the extra slash. Just something to be aware
    of...
    http://stackoverflow.com/questions/7289481/urlparse-urlparse-returning-3-instead-of-2-after-scheme

    Decide if events are down (not reporting data)
    
    Done during upcoming match cronjob. Basic idea is that X minutes have
    passed since the match was scheduled to take place and still no result,
    then the event is down. Update a sitevar with those keys

    will not catch it. Logic will need some tweaking.

    Make event alliances endpoint cronjob run more often
    
    Accomplishes a wish-list item from #1191. The event alliances endpoint
    cronjob now runs every 5 minutes, but event endpoints are only actually
    hit that often on the final day of each event. This way alliance
    selection notifications can go out more quickly with minimal
    extra load.

    Also simplify and link to the Android code to make it easier to keep them
    in sync. E.g. '(.*)' is as good as '(.*)(FIRST Robotics|FRC)?' since the

Author: Phil Lopreiato <plnyyanks@gmail.com>
Date:   2015-01-18 14:04:55 -0500

    Remove option to only send to webhooks
    
    This is impossible with the way things are currently set up.
    Since we use .IN(list) to find subscriptions that match a list of
    possible keys, we can't guarantee which subscription will actually be
    returned (so we can't know if the user is actually explicitely
    subscribed to an event).

Author: Kunal Mehta <legoktm@gmail.com>
Date:   2014-04-13 21:43:40 -0700

    Insights: Use collections.defaultdict
    
    A lot of code right now is in the pattern of:
    
    if foo in bar:
        bar[foo] += 1
    else:
        bar[foo] = 1
    
    This can easily be simplified with defaultdict, which was specifically
    designed for this very purpose.

commit 593c103b30ba365c3a59566f69ba8763800058aa
Author: Greg Marra <greg.marra@gmail.com>
Date:   2013-03-17 19:27:37 -0700

    Adds Create Test Events button to Admin index page.
    
    This button does a lot.
    - It sets up a Past Test Event with complete qualifications.
    - It sets up a Present Test Event with some complete and some incomplete qualifications, as well as a webcast.
    - It sets up a Future Test Event
    
    For each Event
    - The Event has EventTeams generated from Teams already in the dev instance, so you can actually click around the site pretty normally.
    - Since there are matches, you can test things like Insights, Match pages, etc.
    - The webcast lets you check the watch now buttons on teams, event pages, and the homepage
    
    The button does not work in the prod environment.
    
    This diff also refactors some of how testing is done to use the new objects that generate this test data.

commit bf85c133149c96a160b40a64f13c02b9626ad4a9
Author: Greg Marra <greg.marra@gmail.com>
Date:   2012-08-26 14:03:15 -0700

    Moves all FIRST Event datafeeds to the new style Datafeed system.
    
    This system separates parsing from model creation, so should be much easier to test with offline tests. The new model is less forgiving of incorrect data being passed around, throwing more exceptions if you're not using it right (like string years). The new system also is a bit more organized about how parameters are passed in, always taking 'year' first, if it's a required param, for example.
    
    Next up will be moving the other datafeeds over to this model, building their tests, then fixing the terrible Controllers and routing that is the Datafeed system.

commit 2d839dcecbb52f13adf392e9248e98728b2978a9
Author: Greg Marra <greg.marra@gmail.com>
Date:   2012-08-25 15:33:00 -0700

    Use @property for model data methods.
    
    Generally fixes the "prepare_json" pattern, and makes accessing things that are really properties of models, even though they're not stored in the database, look like just accessing their properties. Also changed a few places that were getting a model.key().name() to just get model.key_name now that that's a simple property. More room to improve that, but not in this commit.
